FBIS3-44269 "drafr019_b_94004" FBIS-AFR-94-019 Document Type:Daily Report 29 Jan 1994 EAST AFRICA Tanzania Army Leadership Reshuffled; Diplomat to France Appointed EA2701203094 Dar es Salaam Radio Tanzania Network in Swahili 1700 GMT 27 Jan 94 EA2701203094 Dar es Salaam Radio Tanzania Network Language: Swahili Article Type:BFN [Text] The commander-in-chief of the Armed Forces, President Ali Hassan Mwinyi, has appointed Major General Robert (Mboma) as the new commander of the Tanzanian People's Defense Forces, TPDF, in place of General (Amos Sitiyaro). At the same time he appointed Maj. Gen. (Gideon Ntumbi) Kayore as deputy commander of the Tanzanian People's Defense Forces in place of Lieutenant General Tumainieli Kiwelu, who has been appointed ambassador to France.
